line_1: Who grow more Stubborn when Carest,
line_2: Thus stated Laws are always best

line_1: Who grow more Stubborn when Carest,
Even Love, who lives by Beauty's smiles carest,
line_2: Basks in her eyes, and wantons on her breast,
"Celestial hope sits smiling at their breast; "

line_1: If this, the chief, be not carest;
line_2: But vain the value of the rest,

line_1: But those who have me most carest;
line_2: Will say I grateful am at least;

line_1: Sweet bud of hope, beloved, carest,
line_2: Upon thy head Heaven's blessing rest!

line_1: Who, tho' he sees his foes carest,
line_2: Like some fond lover, hopes the best;
None more the Ladies smiles possest;

line_1: And is it not right they should all be carest
line_2: When they're all so polite and so very well drest;

line_1: E'en Young himself, distinguish'd, lov'd, carest,
line_2: Mark'd by each eye, and hugg'd to every breast,

line_1: Heedless what wit's cashier'd, what sool's carest,
line_2: Who lives an hero, or who lives a jest,
